23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Statute of limitations for surety bonds. (1) On an action relating to a
24 surety appearance bond, the period to commence an action is 2 years. The 2-year period begins on the date
25 the bond is executed.
26 (2) The SURETY appearance bond must be exonerated and discharged after 2 years, regardless of
27 the status of the court case, unless otherwise agreed ON by the surety bail BOND agent.
28 (3) Courts may require a defendant to:
